bootloader:
    - config file
    - muliboot options
    - graphical os selecting interface
    - giving font array from file to kernel

kernel:
    - determine heap size by total memory size
    - page/swap file
    - add support for dynamic linking
    - start shell if no processes are running
    - compability with glibc
    - inter process comunication

makefile:
    - auto detect object files
    - use hdiutil create (need fat32)

filesystem:
    - edit/write with long files
    - rename
    - remove
    - create

    - fat32 implementation (https://www.cs.fsu.edu/~cop4610t/assignments/project3/spec/fatspec.pdf)
    - dos partition table

    - own filesystem (?)

shell:
    - interpreted shell
    - cd command
    - setting env variables (alredy working in the kernel)
    - pipes
    - >> and << operator
    - background tasks
    - multiple tty's
    - exit command